  "texts": [
    "While only a small percentage about 5% of POFA has strong pozzolanic properties, it is still effectively utilized as a SCM.",
    "The quality and effectiveness of POFA largely depend on the specific features of the mill boiler systems where it is produced [39].",
    "Agricultural waste production is on the rise, leading to significant challenges in waste management across many countries.",
    "A study by Krishnan et al. [29] explored the potential of incorporating agricultural waste materials into concrete, with an emphasis on environmentally friendly alternatives.",
    "One such material is GGPA, derived from the plant Vigna radiata, commonly known as mung bean in India."
  ]
